ted output.","API request examples, sample responses, and at least one documented error case.","Validation evidence such as tests, screenshots, logs, query results, metrics, traces, or review notes.","Short reflection on trade-offs, limitations, and one reasonable next improvement."],"reviewFocus":["Does the artifact directly match the project brief?","Can another person run, inspect, or review the result from the provided notes?","Are assumptions, limitations, and trade-offs stated clearly?"],"scopeGuardrails":["Keep the implementation focused on the stated project brief.","Prefer a complete small artifact over a broad unfinished system.","Treat completion as reviewable evidence, not a certification claim."],"claimLimit":"Completion creates reviewable project evidence. It does not certify mastery or guarantee job readiness.","evidenceRequired":true,"optionalPractice":true,"milestone":false,"source":"roadmap.sh/backend","nodeKey":"proj-scale-resilience"}'::jsonb, false, true, '["Apply Circuit Breaker, Failure Modes, Throttling through a focused Resilience Drill artifact.","Explain the main design, data, tooling, workflow, or review decisions behind the project.","Validate the result with evidence that another person can inspect.","Document assumptions, limitations, and a concrete follow-up improvement."]'::jsonb, '["The a runnable Resilience Drill service or API with documented requests and validation behavior is available for review.","The Resilience Drill scope, setup path, input data or scenario, and expected output are documented.","The main workflow runs or can be inspected through a notebook, repository, dashboard, prototype, report, configuration, or case study.","Validation evidence is included and directly relates to the project brief.","The notes identify trade-offs, limitations, and one next improvement without claiming mastery or job readiness."]'::jsonb),
('ph-devops-infra', NULL, 21, 'phase', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Basic Infrastructure and DevOps Awareness', 'Foundational infrastructure and DevOps awareness, with links to deeper DevOps learning.', 'Phase grouping for Basic Infrastructure and DevOps Awareness.', 'trunk', 'roadmap-main', 21, 1, NULL, NULL, 100, 500, 10920, '{"source":"roadmap.sh/backend","nodeKey":"ph-devops-infra"}'::jsonb, true, false, '["Basic Infrastructure and DevOps Awareness"]'::jsonb, '["Required child topics are completed"]'::jsonb),
('grp-infra-devops', 'ph-devops-infra', 1, 'choice_group', NULL, 'complete_all', NULL, 'Basic Infrastructure Knowledge', 'Servers, networks, DNS, TLS, containers, cloud, secrets, and operational ownership.', 'Basic Infrastructure Knowledge groups related backend roadmap topics.', 'side', 'ph-devops-infra-groups', 1, 1, NULL, NULL, 90, 330, 240, '{"progressRule":"complete_all","source":"roadmap.sh/backend","nodeKey":"grp-infra-devops"}'::jsonb, true, false, '["Basic Infrastructure Knowledge"]'::jsonb, '["Required child topics are completed"]'::jsonb),
('infrastructure-basics', 'grp-infra-devops', 1, 'topic', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Basic Infrastructure Knowledge', 'Understand servers, DNS, firewalls, TLS, reverse proxies, containers, cloud regions, managed services, and secrets.', 'Basic Infrastructure Knowledge is a concrete backend roadmap topic.', 'choice', 'grp-infra-devops-topics', 1, 1, 5, 'intermediate', 80, 330, 240, '{"source":"roadmap.sh/backend","nodeKey":"infrastructure-basics"}'::jsonb, true, true, '["Explain how Basic Infrastructure Knowledge affects practical backend engineering work.", "Apply Basic Infrastructure Knowledge to implement backend features or evaluate an implementation decision.", "Identify common mistakes, trade-offs, and signals that the approach is working."]'::jsonb, '["Create concise notes or a diagram explaining Basic Infrastructure Knowledge in context.", "Use the concept to produce a small applied example or decision note.", "Explain at least two trade-offs, risks, or debugging signals related to the topic."]'::jsonb),
('devops-awareness', 'grp-infra-devops', 2, 'topic', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'DevOps Beginner Roadmap Awareness', 'Know when to continue into DevOps topics: Linux, networking, cloud, CI/CD, containers, IaC, observability, and incident response.', 'DevOps Beginner Roadmap Awareness is a concrete backend roadmap topic.', 'choice', 'grp-infra-devops-topics', 1, 2, 3, 'beginner', 45, 540, 360, '{"source":"roadmap.sh/backend","nodeKey":"devops-awareness"}'::jsonb, false, true, '["Explain how DevOps Beginner Roadmap Awareness affects practical backend engineering work.", "Apply DevOps Beginner Roadmap Awareness to implement backend features or evaluate an implementation decision.", "Identify common mistakes, trade-offs, and signals that the approach is working."]'::jsonb, '["Create concise notes or a diagram explaining DevOps Beginner Roadmap Awareness in context.", "Use the concept to prepare a small configuration, deployment note, or operations checklist.", "Explain at least two trade-offs, risks, or debugging signals related to the topic."]'::jsonb),
('gate-final-review', 'ph-devops-infra', 80, 'checkpoint', 'gate', NULL, NULL, 'Final Backend Roadmap Review Gate', 'Final roadmap checkpoint for Basic Infrastructure and DevOps Awareness. The learner reviews portfolio evidence, unresolved gaps, and next learning priorities across the backend engineering path.', 'This checkpoint closes the suggested backend engineering orientation path by organizing evidence and next steps. It is not an employment guarantee or formal competency certification.', 'checkpoint', 'ph-devops-infra-gates', 99, 80, 1, 'intermediate', 100, 500, 11440, '{"gate": true, "reviewRequired": true, "source": "roadmap.sh/backend", "nodeKey": "gate-final-review", "checkpointPurpose": "phase_review", "reviewMode": "final_review", "evidenceRequired": true, "claimLimit": "orientation_and_progress_review_only_not_certification"}'::jsonb, true, true, '["Connect completed roadmap work to a coherent backend engineering learning narrative.", "Review portfolio or project evidence and identify which artifacts are ready to share.", "Define remaining gaps and future specialization priorities."]'::jsonb, '["Summarize completed phases, projects, and major skill groups.", "Attach or reference portfolio evidence, project links, diagrams, reports, tests, or notes where available.", "List remaining gaps or specialization topics for future learning.", "State that the checkpoint is a planning review, not proof of job readiness."]'::jsonb),
('proj-capstone-backend-platform', 'ph-devops-infra', 90, 'project', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Required Backend Capstone Project', 'Capstone project: Build and document a production-style backend API with auth, PostgreSQL, migrations, tests, OpenAPI docs, Docker, CI, caching awareness, and observability notes.', 'This project gives learners a concrete way to practice Basic Infrastructure and DevOps Awareness by producing a portfolio-ready Backend Capstone Project case study and integrated artifact. The artifact is intended for review and reflection, not as proof of mastery or job readiness.', 'checkpoint', 'ph-devops-infra-projects', 99, 90, 18, 'advanced', 75, 120, 10920, '{"project":true,"projectBrief":"Build and document a production-style backend API with auth, PostgreSQL, migrations, tests, OpenAPI docs, Docker, CI, caching awareness, and observability notes.","projectKind":"portfolio_capstone","projectScope":"portfolio_capstone","projectPurpose":"Integrate several roadmap areas into a portfolio-ready case study.","phaseContext":"Basic Infrastructure and DevOps Awareness","deliverable":"a portfolio-ready Backend Capstone Project case study and integrated artifact","skillsToPractice":["Authentication","CI/CD","Docker","Observability"],"suggestedSteps":["Define the Backend Capstone Project scenario and list the specific items to demonstrate: API behavior, authentication and authorization, container setup, CI checks.","Choose a coherent product or case-study scenario that can integrate the strongest projects from the roadmap.","Define the architecture, data or workflow model, user path, and review evidence before implementation.","Build the core artifact end-to-end with scoped features rather than disconnected demos.","Add validation evidence appropriate to the role, such as tests, metrics, query checks, playtest notes, traces, screenshots, or incident notes.","Prepare a case study explaining decisions, trade-offs, limitations, and what would need further review for real deployment.","Package the repository or artifact so another person can reproduce or inspect the result.","Create a review checklist that connects the artifact to the relevant skills and roadmap segment.","Write a limitation and risk section so the project is presented as reviewable evidence, not a certification claim."],"expectedEvidence":["a portfolio-ready Backend Capstone Project case study and integrated artifact.","README or notes that explain setup, usage, assumptions, and expected output.","Case study page or write-up that connects the artifact to role-relevant decisions and evidence.","Validation evidence such as tests, screenshots, logs, query results, metrics, traces, or review notes.","Short reflection on trade-offs, limitations, and one reasonable next improvement.","Architecture, review checklist, and limitation section suitable for portfolio discussion."],"reviewFocus":["Does the artifact directly match the project brief?","Can another person run, inspect, or review the result from the provided notes?","Are assumptions, limitations, and trade-offs stated clearly?"],"scopeGuardrails":["Keep the implementation focused on the stated project brief.","Prefer a complete small artifact over a broad unfinished system.","Treat completion as reviewable evidence, not a certification claim."],"claimLimit":"Completion creates reviewable project evidence. It does not certify mastery or guarantee job readiness.","evidenceRequired":true,"optionalPractice":false,"milestone":true,"source":"roadmap.sh/backend","nodeKey":"proj-capstone-backend-platform"}'::jsonb, true, true, '["Apply Authentication, CI/CD, Docker through a focused Backend Capstone Project artifact.","Integrate multiple roadmap areas into one coherent case study rather than isolated exercises.","Explain the main design, data, tooling, workflow, or review decisions behind the project.","Validate the result with evidence that another person can inspect.","Document assumptions, limitations, and a concrete follow-up improvement."]'::jsonb, '["The a portfolio-ready Backend Capstone Project case study and integrated artifact is available for review.","The Backend Capstone Project scope, setup path, input data or scenario, and expected output are documented.","The main workflow runs or can be inspected through a notebook, repository, dashboard, prototype, report, configuration, or case study.","The case study connects implementation decisions to relevant roadmap skills and explains why alternatives were not chosen.","Validation evidence is included and directly relates to the project brief.","The notes identify trade-offs, limitations, and one next improvement without claiming mastery or job readiness.","The project is packaged so a reviewer can understand the artifact without live mentoring."]'::jsonb)
;

INSERT INTO public.roadmap_node
(roadmap_node_id, roadmap_version_id, parent_node_id, slug, node_type, checkpoint_type, selection_type, required_count, title, description, reason, order_index, layout_role, layout_group, layout_rank, layout_order, estimated_hours, difficulty_level, priority, position_x, position_y, metadata, is_required, is_trackable, learning_outcomes, completion_criteria)
SELECT
    sn.node_id,
    m.roadmap_version_id,
    parent.node_id,
    sn.node_key,
    sn.node_type,
    sn.checkpoint_type,
    sn.selection_type,
    sn.required_count,
    sn.title,
    sn.description,
    sn.reason,
    sn.order_index,
    sn.layout_role,
    sn.layout_group,
    sn.layout_rank,
    sn.layout_order,
    sn.estimated_hours,
    sn.difficulty_level,
    sn.priority,
    sn.position_x,
    sn.position_y,
    sn.metadata,
    sn.is_required,
    sn.is_trackable,
    sn.learning_outcomes,
    sn.completion_criteria
FROM seed_node sn
CROSS JOIN seed_roadmap_map m
LEFT JOIN seed_node parent ON parent.node_key = sn.parent_key
ON CONFLICT (roadmap_version_id, slug) DO UPDATE SET
    parent_node_id = EXCLUDED.parent_node_id,
    node_type = EXCLUDED.node_type,
    checkpoint_type = EXCLUDED.checkpoint_type,
    selection_type = EXCLUDED.selection_type,
    required_count = EXCLUDED.required_count,
    title = EXCLUDED.title,
    description = EXCLUDED.description,
    reason = EXCLUDED.reason,
    order_index = EXCLUDED.order_index,
    layout_role = EXCLUDED.layout_role,
    layout_group = EXCLUDED.layout_group,
    layout_rank = EXCLUDED.layout_rank,
    layout_order = EXCLUDED.layout_order,
    estimated_hours = EXCLUDED.estimated_hours,
    difficulty_level = EXCLUDED.difficulty_level,
    priority = EXCLUDED.priority,
    position_x = EXCLUDED.position_x,
    position_y = EXCLUDED.position_y,
    metadata = EXCLUDED.metadata,
    is_required = EXCLUDED.is_required,
    is_trackable = EXCLUDED.is_trackable,
    learning_outcomes = EXCLUDED.learning_outcomes,
    completion_criteria = EXCLUDED.completion_criteria;

